THE ELECTION OF 1968
The 1968 presidential election, which Richard Nixon won, was almost as close as the election of 1960, which he had lost. Nixon might have won a more su stantia victory had it not been for the independent candidacy of Governor George C. a ace, w o attracted many of the same conservative voters to whom Nixon appealed.
