radicalism in mainstream culture was one of chaos and disorder, based in part on the disruptive actions of small groups of militants, among them the "Weathermen,” a violent offshoot of SDS. The Weathermen were responsible for several cases of arson and bombing that destroyed campus buildings and claimed several lives. Not many people, not even many students, ever accepted the most radical political views that lay at the heart of the New Left. But many supported the position of SDS and other groups on particular issues and, above all, on the Vietnam War. Student activists tried to drive out training programs for military officers (ROTC) and bar military
